TY  - JOUR
AU  - Marshall, Ellen R.
T1  - A Primer on Securitization
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/revfin/12.3.0648
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
SP  - 648
EP  - 652
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The prospect of introducing securitization to a novice — whether it be a newly minted graduate of business or law school, or a seasoned CFO of a corporation that is considering its first securitization — is daunting. The elegance of the theoretical concept becomes quickly mired in the interdependent demands of accounting, taxation, bankruptcy and securities laws, and the ever-changing contours of the investor marketplace as soon as the novice begins to ask questions. Successful completion of real-world securitization transactions requires not only cooperation among professionals in a variety of disciplines, but an intimate understanding of the parameters of those disciplines. The prospect of a primer that would provide a first glimpse of the contours of this terrain would be a welcome addition to the library of many a law firm, accounting firm, or investment bank.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/revfin/12.3.0648
ER  - 



